## 🎯 Real-World Use Cases

* Finding publicly accessible files
* Discovering backup/config files
* Identifying weak credentials
* Mapping attack surface

---

## ⚠️ Common Misconfigurations Found

* Anonymous login enabled
* Writable directories
* Weak passwords
* Outdated FTP software

---

## 🛡️ Defensive Measures

To secure FTP services:

* Disable anonymous login
* Use strong authentication
* Restrict file permissions
* Prefer secure alternatives like SFTP
* Keep software updated

---

## ⚖️ Legal Considerations

Always ensure proper authorization before performing enumeration using Nmap. Unauthorized scanning may be illegal.

---

## 📚 Conclusion

Nmap NSE scripts provide a powerful way to automate FTP enumeration. By combining multiple scripts, you can quickly uncover misconfigurations, sensitive data exposure, and potential vulnerabilities in FTP services.

